Import libraries

library(rethinking)
Review of prior pediction using the milk data of chapter 5


Import data

# Import the data
data(rugged)
d <- rugged


Preprocessing

d$log_gdp <- log(d$rgdppc_2000)
dd <- d[ complete.cases(d$rgdppc_2000) , ]
dd$log_gdp_std <- dd$log_gdp / mean(dd$log_gdp)
dd$rugged_std <- dd$rugged / max(dd$rugged)
dd$cid <- ifelse( dd$cont_africa==1 , 1 , 2 )


Build a model

m8.3 <- quap(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a[cid] + b[cid]*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a[cid] ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b[cid] ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
    ) , data=dd )
precis( m8.3 , depth=2 )
##             mean          sd        5.5%       94.5%
## a[1]   0.8865644 0.015675372  0.86151210  0.91161664

Extract the data to train MCMC

dat_slim <- list(
    log_gdp_std = dd$log_gdp_std,
    rugged_std = dd$rugged_std,
    cid = as.integer( dd$cid )
)
str(dat_slim)
## List of 3
##  $ log_gdp_std: num [1:170] 0.88 0.965 1.166 1.104 0.915 ...
##  $ rugged_std : num [1:170] 0.138 0.553 0.124 0.125 0.433 ...
##  $ cid        : int [1:170] 1 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 1 ...


Build a MCMC model, with one chain

m9.1 <- ulam(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a[cid] + b[cid]*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a[cid] ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b[cid] ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
    ) , data=dat_slim , chains=1 )


Inspect the result

precis( m9.1 , depth=2 )

Build a MCMC model, with four chain

m9.1 <- ulam(
    alist(
        log_gdp_std ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a[cid] + b[cid]*( rugged_std - 0.215 ) ,
        a[cid] ~ dnorm( 1 , 0.1 ) ,
        b[cid] ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.3 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
    ) , data=dat_slim , chains=4 , cores=4 )


Inspect the training details

show(m9.1)
